            <fr:title text="Intermdiated value property equivalent to being connected">Intermdiated value property equivalent to being connected</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>proposition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(X,\mathcal {T})]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="/gt-0002/" title="Topological space" uri="http://localhost:8000/gt-0002/" display-uri="gt-0002" type="local">Topological space</fr:link>. Then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> has <fr:link href="/gt-000W/" title="Intermediate Value Property" uri="http://localhost:8000/gt-000W/" display-uri="gt-000W" type="local">Intermediate Value Property</fr:link> if and only if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="/gt-000T/" title="Connected Space" uri="http://localhost:8000/gt-000T/" display-uri="gt-000T" type="local">Connected Space</fr:link>.</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/alex-nelson/" title="Alex Nelson" uri="http://localhost:8000/alex-nelson/" display-uri="alex-nelson" type="local">Alex Nelson</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>12</fr:month><fr:day>12</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><html:p><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(\Longleftarrow )]]></fr:tex> Since <fr:link href="/gt-000V/" title="Continuous image of a connected subset is connected" uri="http://localhost:8000/gt-000V/" display-uri="gt-000V" type="local">Continuous image of a connected subset is connected</fr:link>, the result follows immediately (if one has already proven intervals of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex> are connected).</html:p>
<html:p><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(\Longrightarrow )]]></fr:tex> <fr:link href="/nst-002I/" title="Proof by contrapositive" uri="http://localhost:8000/nst-002I/" display-uri="nst-002I" type="local">Proof by contrapositive</fr:link>. We prove the contrapositive; i.e., we prove the equivalent claim if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is not connected, then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> does not have the intermediate value property. Since <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is not connected, let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U_{1},U_{2}\subseteq  X]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="/gt-000S/" title="Separated space" uri="http://localhost:8000/gt-000S/" display-uri="gt-000S" type="local">separation</fr:link>. Define a function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  X\to \mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex> by
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[f(x) = \begin {cases}0 & \hbox {if }x\in  U_{1}\\
1 & \hbox {if }x\in  U_{2}.\end {cases}]]></fr:tex>
Then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is continuous, since for every open subset <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A\subseteq \mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex>, the preimage <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f^{-1}(A)]]></fr:tex> is open (by <fr:link href="/gt-000Q/" title="A function is continuous iff preimage of open subsets are open" uri="http://localhost:8000/gt-000Q/" display-uri="gt-000Q" type="local">A function is continuous iff preimage of open subsets are open</fr:link>). However, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f(X)]]></fr:tex> is not an interval, so we found a counter-example needed to conclude <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> fails to have the intermediate value property.</html:p><html:span class="qed">âˆŽ</html:span></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
